  "market_context": "Indices triad comparison with NQ on the left and YM on the right. YM sweeps the range low at the 9:00 AM equities open, while NQ fails to make a corresponding lower low, setting up a bullish reversal looking to trade back to the range high.",
  "key_observation": "The SMT divergence between NQ and YM at the range low is immediately confirmed by a precision swing point printed exactly on the 9:00 AM candle close, pairing a session driver (equities open) with a reversal signature.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify YM running the range low while NQ does not make a corresponding lower low, establishing SMT divergence.",
    "Step 2: Note the target as the range high since price swept the range low.",
    "Step 3: Confirm the SMT with a precision swing point (PSP) printed on the same candle.",
    "Step 4: Highlight the timing — PSP prints on the 9:00 AM candle close, which is the equities open driver.",
    "Step 5: Wait for candle 2 closure to confirm the reversal.",
    "Step 6: Seek a 10:00 AM candle 3 continuation entry; once candle 3 closes strongly, look for candle 4 continuation into the range high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Analyst took this trade on YM, riding candle 3 strong closure into a candle 4 continuation targeting the range high.",
  "lessons": "Pairing a session driver (9:00 AM equities open) with a reversal signature (SMT + PSP) significantly increases reversal probability. Timing of the PSP is what elevates this setup beyond a standard SMT.",
